President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Katherine Archuleta as the Director of the Office of Personnel Management (OPM). If confirmed, she will be the first Latina to head the agency. Archuleta has a broad range of experience, having served as the National Political Director for Obama for America from 2011 to 2012 and as Chief of Staff at the U.S. Department of Labor from 2009 to 2011. She has also held positions in the City and County of Denver, the National Hispanic Cultural Center Foundation, and Davis, Graham and Stubbs, LLP. Archuleta has a B.A. from Metropolitan State College and a M.Ed. from the University of Northern Colorado. President Obama praised her experience and commitment to recruiting and retaining a world-class workforce for the American people.